            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It seems that `buf` also needs to be mentioned. Initially, `vim.pos()` did not have `buf` as a mandatory argument, but now it serves as the essential first parameter; we need to update the docs. Perhaps it should also be mentioned that `vim.pos` represents \"a position on a buffer\" rather than just \"a well-defined position.\"",
            "commit_id": "68336241a11d048c9b4fcc0360cb6c48509af7b2",
            "created_at": "2026-05-22T08:41:58Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -4479,10 +4479,9 @@ by |vim.Pos| objects.\n \n \n *vim.Pos*\n-    Represents a well-defined position.\n-\n-    A |vim.Pos| object contains the {row} and {col} coordinates of a position.\n-    To create a new |vim.Pos| object, call `vim.pos()`.\n+    Represents a well-defined position based on |api-indexing| (0-indexed,\n+    ranges are end-exclusive). Call `vim.pos()` to create a new `vim.Pos`\n+    position by passing the {row} and {col} coordinates of a position.",
